textBeforeTable: Cylinders: For more specific information, please read the Advisory Notices, which can be viewed, printed and downloaded at www.teleflexmarine.com When ordering, please refer to the appropriate SeaStar part number for the item in question. This table indicates which SeaStar part numbers have superseded the Hynautic steering items that are no longer available. Hynautic-SeaStar Cross-Reference See also SeaStar Selection Guide (Document #SL6001) and Document #971715. NOTE: #10 screws used to mount bulkhead flanges are customer supplied. For SeaStar PRO systems, use only SeaStar PRO hoses. Use only SeaStar or SeaStar PRO outboard hoses with SeaStar outboard systems. Do not mount bulkhead fitting below static float plane of boat. This is not a fluid tight fitting. Bulkhead Hoses The following chart lists hose or tubing requirements for BayStar, Capilano, SeaStar and Hynautic hydraulic steering systems. Purchase of additional fitting kits may be required for some installations. Can be used with all SeaStar systems with fitting kit and flexible cylinder hoses, except stern drives using SeaStar 1.7 helms and/or HC5332 cylinders. Copper tubing is recommended for inboard systems; do not use on outboard systems. COPPER TUBING HT5100 100' x 3/8" HT5097 75' x 38" HT5095 50'
